Title: Translation Is a Second Narration (Sample)

This is the original English source text for the default translation sample shown in the Aither translations section.

It exists as a stable source link so the translated article can show a proper "read original" reference without turning the translations shelf back into a multilingual publishing section.

Translation is not duplication. When meaning moves between languages, tone, emphasis, structure, and context all need to be retold with care.

That is why this sample frames translation as a second narration: not a literal mirror, but a disciplined retelling that lets the source idea live clearly in another language.
